3EFor%202024%20taxes%2C%20the%20Child%20Tax%20Credit%20is%20worth%20up%20to%20%242%2C000%20per%20qualifying%20child.%20The%20maximum%20income%20you%20can%20have%20to%20qualify%20for%20the%20credit%20(%24200%2C000)%20is%20the%20same%20for%20all%20filing%20statuses%2C%20except%20married%20joint%20filers%20(%24400%2C000).%20Up%20to%20%241%2C700%20of%20the%20credit%20is%20refundable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20no%20maximum%20income%20threshold%20for%20claiming%20the%20Child%20and%20Dependent%20Care%20Credit%2C%20which%20allows%20you%20to%20write%20off%20some%20expenses%20associated%20with%20the%20care%20of%20a%20child%20under%2013%20or%20a%20dependent%20of%20any%20age%20who%20is%20mentally%20or%20physically%20disabled.%20Once%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Fwhat-is-adjusted-gross-income-agi-taxes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadjusted%20gross%20income%2C%20or%20AGI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reaches%20%2443%2C000%2C%20regardless%20of%20filing%20status%2C%20your%20maximum%20credit%20is%20either%20%24300%20for%20one%20qualifying%20dependent%20or%20%24600%20for%20two%20or%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228cc84087-e04d-4f0a-99b0-f45c27935dcf%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20to%20claim%20head%20of%20household%20status%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20claim%20head%20of%20household%20status%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224b9ce084-ced6-44bd-bf3b-90f268734ac3%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Gathering%20necessary%20documentation%5C%22%3EGathering%20necessary%20documentation%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFiling%20taxes%20as%20head%20of%20household%20can%20be%20more%20involved%20than%20filing%20as%20single.%20You%E2%80%99ll%20need%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irs.gov%2Fpub%2Firs-pdf%2Ff14824.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprovide%20supporting%20documents%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20confirm%20your%20marital%20status%20and%20the%20eligibility%20of%20your%20dependent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20prove%20qualifying%