ols%20or%20restoring%20roads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20main%20types%20of%20muni%20bonds%20are%20revenue%20and%20general%20obligation.%20Revenue%20bonds%20can%20be%20slightly%20riskier%20because%20repayment%20relies%20on%20revenue%20from%20a%20specific%20project%20or%20source.%20Repayment%20of%20general%20obligation%20bonds%20comes%20from%20the%20issuing%20state%20or%20local%20government%2C%20which%20can%20raise%20taxes%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20bonds%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220640c28b-f1b9-4552-95e5-77643e105f21%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Tax%20advantages%5C%22%3ETax%20advantages%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EUsually%2C%20bondholders%20receive%20two%20interest%2C%20or%20coupon%2C%20payments%20a%20year%2C%20which%20are%20not%20subject%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Fwhat-is-federal-income-tax%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20income%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20a%20set%20period%20of%20time%2C%20bondholders%20receive%20their%20original%20investment%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20can%20buy%20muni%20bonds%20from%20the%20state%20or%20locality%20in%20which%20they%20reside%2C%20or%20from%20another%20state%20or%20locality.%20Typically%20interest%20income%20from%20muni%20bonds%20%E2%80%94%20or%20muni%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investor.gov%2Fintroduction-investing%2Finvesting-basics%2Fglossary%2Fbond-funds-and-income-funds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebond%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20issued%20by%20your%20home%20state%20is%20not%20taxable%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ec0e7ea7-6994-4387-91d6-68b4a46dc6fa%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Risks%20and%20considerations%5C%22%3ERisks%20and%20considerations%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20muni%20bond%20interest%20income%20may%20not%20be%20fully%20tax-exempt%20at%20home%20if%20you%20buy%20an%20out-of-state%20bond%2C%20says%20Derrick%20Doerr%2C%20a%20CPA%20and%20vice%20president%20at%20financial-services%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nepsisinc.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENepsis%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Minneapolis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EState%20rules%20vary%2C%20but%20generally%2C%20the%20interest%20you%20earn%20from%20an%20out-of-state%20bond%20can%20trigger%20taxes%20in%20your%20home%20state.%20Exceptions%20include%20Washington%20D.C.%20and%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Fstates-with-no-income-tax-map%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estates%20with%20no%20income%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20Doerr%20notes%2C%20%26quot%3BMunicipal%20bonds%20are%20generally%20low%20risk%2C%20but%20not%20risk-free.%26quot%3B%20One%20risk%20is%20that%20muni%20bonds%20can%20be%20called%20early%20by%20the%20issuer.%20This%20often%20happens%20when%20interest%20rates%20fall%2C%20and%20can%20leave%20an%20investor%20choosing%20from%20lower-paying%20alternatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20high%20earner%2C%20there's%20something%20else%20to%20consider%3A%20Interest%20from%20private%20activity%20bonds%2C%20a%20type%20of%20muni%20bond%20issued%20by%20a%20private%20business%20and%20not%20a%20government%20entity%2C%20may%20not%20be%20tax-exempt%20if%20you%20pay%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftaxfoundation.org%2Ftaxedu%2Fglossary%2Falternative-minimum-tax-amt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlternative%20Minimum%20Tax%3C%2Fa%3E%20(AMT).%20AMT%20may%20apply%20to%20individuals%20with%20incomes%20over%20%24609%2C350%20or%20married%20couples%20filing%20jointly%20with%20incomes%20above%20about%20%241.2%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENote%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20U.S.%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investor.gov%2Fintroduction-investing%2Fgeneral-resources%2Fnews-alerts%2Falerts-bulletins%2Finvestor-bulletins-37%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecommends%3C%2Fa%3E%20reading%20official%20statements%20and%20disclosures%20from%20bond%20issuers%20and%20reviewing%20trade%20prices%20of%20municipal%20bonds%20you%20are%20considering%20buying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22adbf3058-0334-4686-a141-7047e9b234d9%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Tax-exempt%20interest%20from%20U.S.%20Treasury%20Securities%5C%22%3ETax-exempt%20interest%20from%20U.S.%20Treasury%20Securities%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221eee23bd-8da5-4e40-8b97-092378179cbf%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20Are%20U.S.%20Treasury%20Securities%3F%5C%22%3EWhat%20Are%20U.S.%20Treasury%20Securities%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETax-exempt%20interest%20income%20can%20also%20come%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Ftreasury-bonds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EU.S.%20Treasury%20Securities%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Interest%20is%20paid%20semiannually%20and%20subject%20to%20federal%20taxation%2C%20but%20exempt%20from%20state%20and%20local%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETreasurys%20are%20backed%20by%20the%20federal%20government%20and%20are%20categorized%20by%20their%20maturities%2C%20or%20how%20long%20it%20takes%20to%20return%20your%20original%20investment%20(principal).%20Bills%20mature%20within%20a%20year%2C%20notes%20mature%20within%2010%20years%2C%20and%20bonds%20mature%20in%2020%20or%2030%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETreasury%20Inflation%20Protected%20Securities%20(TIPS)%20are%20a%20type%20of%20Treasury%20bond%20that%20protects%20your%20investment%20from%20inflation.%20They're%20available%20in%20terms%20of%20five%2C%2010%2C%20or%2030%20years.%20The%20interest%20rate%20is%20fixed%2C%20and%20semiannual%20payments%20are%20only%20federally%20taxable%2C%20but%20your%20principal%20can%20fluctuate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterest%20earned%20from%20Series%20EE%20and%20Series%20I%20Savings%20Bonds%20are%20also%20exempt%20from%20state%20and%20local%20taxes.%20Interest%2C%20which%20is%20collected%20at%20maturity%20or%20whenever%20you%20cash%20the%20bond%2C%20could%20be%20exempt%20from%20federal%20taxation%20if%20you%20use%20the%20proceeds%20for%20qualified%20higher%20education%20expenses%2C%20though%20several%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.treasurydirect.gov%2Fsavings-bonds%2Ftax-information-ee-i-bonds%2Fusing-bonds-for-higher-education%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erules%3C%2Fa%3E%20apply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221f0680d7-077f-4af7-857d-bdd1cf11e2ae%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Tax%20advantages%5C%22%3ETax%20advantages%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETreasurys%20produce%20fixed%20interest%20that's%20not%20subject%20to%20state%20or%20local%20taxes%2C%20offering%20predictable%20income%20for%20bondholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20T-bonds%2C%20bills%2C%20and%20notes%2C%20you%20have%20to%20include%20the%20interest%20in%20your%20federal%20gross%20income%20each%20year%20that%20you%20collect%20it.%20For%20savings%20bonds%2C%20interest%20isn't%20paid%20until%20the%20bond%20is%20redeemed%2C%20so%20you%20have%20the%20choice%20to%20pay%20federal%20taxes%20on%20it%20in%20the%20year%20you%20collect%20or%20spread%20it%20out%20over%20the%20life%20of%20the%20bond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22db35935e-6658-4fc8-8df1-37b005fdd24b%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Risks%20and%20considerations%5C%22%3ERisks%20and%20considerations%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETreasurys%20are%20the%20closest%20thing%20to%20a%20risk-free%20investment%20since%20they're%20backed%20by%20the%20full%20faith%20and%20credit%20of%20the%20federal%20government.%20But%20you%20still%20owe%20federal%20taxes%20on%20the%20interest%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20risk%20associated%20with%20Treasurys%20is%20in%20how%20long%20they%20take%20to%20mature.%20Interest%20rates%20are%20fixed%20for%20the%20life%20of%20the%20bond%2C%20which%20can%20be%20as%20high%20as%2020%20or%2030%20years%20for%20bonds%20or%20up%20to%2010%20years%20for%20bills.%20If%20interest%20rates%20rise%20on%20newly%20issued%20Treasurys%2C%20the%20value%20of%20existing%20bonds%20drops.%20This%20is%