other%20investments%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20types%20of%20investments%20may%20produce%20a%20kind%20of%20tax-exempt%20interest%20or%20return.%20For%20example%2C%20investment%20gains%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-a-529-plan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E529%20college%20savings%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20not%20taxable%20at%20the%20federal%20or%20state%20levels%20if%20the%20funds%20are%20used%20for%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20some%20might%20consider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRAs%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20tax-exempt%20investment%2C%20since%20the%20accounts%20are%20funded%20with%20posttax%20dollars%2C%20which%20grow%20tax-free%20and%20can%20be%20withdrawn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fira-early-withdrawal-without-penalty%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epenalty-%20and%20tax-free%20under%20certain%20circumstances%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20reaching%20age%2059%20and%20a%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223fc700dd-941e-40a4-aefb-a3cee5a56527%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Taxable%20interest%20vs.%20tax-exempt%20interest%5C%22%3ETaxable%20interest%20vs.%20tax-exempt%20interest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20corporate%20bonds%20have%20higher%20advertised%20interest%20rates%20than%20tax-exempt%20bonds%2C%20but%20the%20interest%20is%20fully%20taxable.%20It%20can%20seem%20like%20a%20no-brainer%2C%20then%2C%20to%20opt%20for%20a%20bond%20that%20gives%20you%20a%20tax%20break%20over%20one%20that%20doesn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20Moore%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20a%20federal%20tax-free%20amount%26quot%3B%20with%20municipal%20bonds.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20look%20at%20the%20states%20and%20you%20have%20to%20look%20at%20somebody's%20complete%20tax%20picture%20to%20see%20if%20it%20makes%20sense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20comparing%20bonds%2C%20investors%20need%20to%20find%20the%20tax-equivalent%20yield%20of%20their%20bond%20options%20to%20see%20which%20produces%20a%20higher%20after-tax%20return%2C%20says%20Doerr.%20A%20specialized%20calculator%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigital.fidelity.com%2Fprgw%2Fdigital%2Ftaxyieldcalc%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTax%252DEquivalent%2520Yield%2520is%2520one%2Con%2520a%2520tax%252Dexempt%2520security.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elike%20this%20one%20from%20Fidelity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20can%20help%20crunch%20the%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20although%20the%20IRS%20(and%20many%20state%20governments)%20exempt%20certain%20interest%20income%20from%20the%20computation%20of%20income%20tax%2C%20those%20amounts%20may%20later%20be%20added%20back%20in%20other%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20federal%20income%20tax%20calculation%20purposes%2C%20tax-exempt%20interest%20is%20added%20back%20to%20figure%20your%20modified%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Fwhat-is-adjusted-gross-income-agi-taxes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadjusted%20gross%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20a%20crucial%20figure%20that%20determines%20deductible%20contributions%20to%20traditional%20IRAs%2C%20eligibility%20for%20a%20Roth%20IRA%2C%20and%20qualification%20for%20education%20credits%2C%20healthcare%20credits%2C%20and%20the%20Child%20Tax%20Credit.%20It's%20also%20used%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20much%20of%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-social-security%23social-security-and-taxes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%20benefits%20are%20taxable%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22710b823d-8317-4f4c-9ca9-3bc8cff1e6ab%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Estimate%20your%20taxes%5C%22%3EEstimate%20your%20taxes%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%