%20dots%20of%20countless%20stars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20the%20second%20day%2C%20we%20trek%20up%20to%20Kala%20Pokhari%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sasang%20informs.%20A%20slightly%20larger%20establishment%2C%20Kala%20Pokhari%20is%20named%20after%20the%20seemingly%20black%20lake%20it%20houses%20(%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EKala%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20meaning%20black%20and%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EPokhari%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20meaning%20lake%20in%20Nepali).%20At%20an%20altitude%20of%203%2C000%20metres%20(9%2C842%20feet)%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20perfect%20place%20to%20rest%20and%20take%20in%20the%20breathtaking%20surroundings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201600px)%20100vw%2C%201600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fs2_11zon-1735043656.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20outline%20of%20the%20Kanchendzonga%20range%20resembling%20'The%20Sleeping%20Buddha'%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fs2_11zon-1735043656.jpeg%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fs2_11zon-1735043656-300x138.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fs2_11zon-1735043656-500x230.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fs2_11zon-1735043656-768x354.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fs2_11zon-1735043656-1536x708.jpeg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fs2_11zon-1735043656-150x69.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-392130%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20outline%20of%20the%20Kanchendzonga%20range%20resembling%20%E2%80%98The%20Sleeping%20Buddha%E2%80%99%3B%20Image%3A%20Jacob%20Subba%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20after%20a%20challenging%20but%20rewarding%20climb%2C%20you%20will%20reach%20the%20summit%20at%20Sandakphu%2C%20a%20vantage%20point%20from%20where%20you%20can%20see%20four%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20five%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F337481%2Fbaljeet-kaur-mountaineer-climber-mt-annapurna-everest-kilimanjaro-himachal-pradesh%2F%23google_vignette%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehighest%20mountains%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20Everest%2C%20Kangchendzonga%2C%20Lhotse%2C%20and%20Makalu.%20Kangchendzonga%2C%20your%20constant%20companion%2C%20would%20stand%20out%20%E2%80%94%20its%20cluster%20making%20up%20a%20golden%20or%20white%20silhouette%20that%20gives%20it%20the%20name%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Sleeping%20Buddha%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%224678180483%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20route%20that%20trekkers%20use%20starts%20from%20Rimbik%2C%20or%20nearby%20Sirikhola%2C%20about%2055%20km%20from%20Darjeeling.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20due%20to%20the%20accessible%20motorable%20road%20we%20have%20nowadays%20that%20we%20choose%20the%20Rimbik%20route%2C%E2%80%9D%20Keshav%20Gurung%2C%20who%20runs%20the%20Shikhar%20Tarry%20homestay%20in%20Mane%20Bhanjyang%2C%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CGroups%20like%20%E2%80%98India%20Hikes%E2%80%99%20regularly%20use%20this%20route.%20They%20drive%20from%20here%20till%20Rimbik%20and%20then%20climb%20up%20from%20the%20other%20side%20through%20Phalut%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhere%20to%20stay%20in%20Sandakphu%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%E2%80%99re%20planning%20a%20trip%20to%20Sandakphu%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20best%20to%20keep%20at%20least%20a%20week%20in%20hand.%20%E2%80%9CFrom%20Sandakphu%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20your%20choice%20whether%20you%20want%20to%20reach%20Phalut%20or%20climb%20down%20through%20Rimbik%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sasang%20says.%20The%20descent%20from%20the%20summit%20ends%20in%20the%20town%20of%20Rimbik%20and%20passes%20through%20Sirikhola.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPhalut%2C%20the%20second-highest%20peak%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20remains%20a%20popular%20spot%20among%20trekkers%20due%20to%20its%20pristine%20location%2C%20breathtaking%20views%2C%20and%20colour%20tapestry%20created%20by%20full-bloom%20rhododendrons.%20Many%20believe%20that%20the%20trek%20to%20Sandakphu%20is%20incomplete%20without%20setting%20foot%20on%20Phalut.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FIMG-20241201-WA0013-1735044127-500x667.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20sunset%20paints%20a%20silhouette%20of%20jeeps%20near%20Sandakphu%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FIMG-20241201-WA0013-1735044127-500x667.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FIMG-20241201-WA0013-1735044127-225x300.jpg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FIMG-20241201-WA0013-1735044127-768x1024.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FIMG-20241201-WA0013-1735044127-1152x1536.jpg%201152w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FIMG-20241201-WA0013-1735044127-640x853.jpg%20640w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FIMG-20241201-WA0013-1735044127-150x200.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FIMG-20241201-WA0013-1735044127.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-392141%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20sunset%20paints%20a%20silhouette%20of%20jeeps%20near%20Sandakphu%3B%20image%3A%20Sasang%20Gurung%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Phalut%20trek%20would%20take%20at%20least%20five%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Sangay%20Sherpa%2C%20who%20manages%20the%20Singalila%20Jungle%20Lodge%20in%20Palmauja%20near%20Dhotrey.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20dearth%20of%20lodging%20throughout%20the%20entire%20journey%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%20Dhotrey%20is%20among%20numerous%20villages%20that%20trekkers%20choose%20to%20acclimatise%20before%20starting%20their%20Sandakphu%20journey.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESasang%20informs%20that%20the%20Singalila%20Ridge%20is%20dotted%20with%20such%20offbeat%20destinations.%20Since%20tourism%20is%20an%20important%20means%20of%20livelihood%2C%20there%20are%20a%20sizable%20number%20of%20homestays%20and%20lodges.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20best%20to%20make%20bookings%20in%20advance%2C%20particularly%20during%20the%20holiday%20season%2C%20Sasang%20recommends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EDoes%20it%20snow%20in%20Sandakphu%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes!%20The%20higher%20altitudes%20have%20traditionally%20been%20blessed%20with%20snowfall%20between%20the%20months%20of%20December%20and%20February.%20However%2C%20it%20has%20become%20a%20tad%20bit%20erratic%2C%20thanks%20to%20climate%20change.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20some%20light%20snowfall%20in%20September%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Sasang.%20%E2%80%9CLast%20year%2C%20it%20snowed%20in%20March.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20inform%20me%20that%20the%20best%20time%20to%20make%20the%20trek%20is%20between%20September%20and%20November%20when%20the%20skies%20are%20crystal%20clear%2C%20or%20March%20and%20April%20when%20the%20forests%20are%20lush.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20up%20for%20it%2C%20any%20time%20is%20a%20good%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%2